# Lumina uses two profile files at the repo root (recommended):
#
#   .env.development  — local machine (copy from .env.development.example)
#   .env.hosting      — hosting / prod-like (copy from .env.hosting.example)
#
# Default commands:
#   pnpm run dev           → development profile + Vite mode development
#   pnpm run dev:hosting   → hosting profile + Vite mode hosting
#
# Legacy: a single `.env` still works if present; it overrides the default profile
# resolution when `LUMINA_PROFILE` is not set.
#
# Override file path entirely:
#   LUMINA_ENV_FILE=/path/to/.env.custom
#
# Only variables prefixed with `VITE_` are exposed to the browser.
